Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} lengthways into 1cm slices, then
chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in
a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Pop
half the onion into a #medium bowl{} and add the @rice vinegar{15}ml, @sugar{1} for the
pickle and a pinch of @salt{}. Mix together, then set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@sesame seeds{15} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, divide them between 2 #small bowls{}. Set one bowl aside. Add the
@mayonnaise{64}ml to the other sesame seed bowl and season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then stir to combine and set aside.

Pop your (now empty) pan back on high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once the oil is hot,
add the @British pork mince{240} and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Use a #spoon{}
to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Add the pepper and remaining onion to the pork and cook, stirring occasionally, for
~{4-5%minutes} more.

When the veg has softened and the pork is cooked through, add the garlic to the pan.
Stir and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @bulgogi sauce{75} and heat
through gently until piping hot, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When you're almost ready to serve, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a baking tray
and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Lay the warmed tortillas on your
#plates{} (3 per person). Spread over a spoonful of sesame mayo on each, then top with
the pork mixture and pickled red onion - as much as you'd like. Sprinkle over the
remaining sesame seeds to finish and serve with the chips alongside. Enjoy!